{{Infobox news event | title = 2004 Arkhangelsk explosion | image = File:Map of Russia - Arkhangelsk Oblast (2008-03).svg | image_size= 250px | caption = Location of Arkhangelsk Oblast in Russia | date = 16 March 2004 | time = 3:03 AM | place = [[Arkhangelsk]], [[Arkhangelsk Oblast]], [[Northwestern Federal District]], [[Russia]] | reported death(s) = 58 }}
On March 16, 2004, an [[explosion]] destroyed a corner section of a nine-story [[Soviet Union|Soviet]]-era apartment building in [[Arkhangelsk, Russia]]. It happened at 3:03&nbsp;a.m. local time ([[UTC]] +3). The explosion occurred in 120 Avenue of the Soviet Cosmonauts in the October district (''Oktyabrskiy rayon'') of Arkhangelsk.
The death toll from the explosion was 58 (33 women, 16 men and 9 children). At least 2 of the dead died in a [[hospital]] after being rescued.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/3522832.stm|title=BBC NEWS - Europe - Search abandoned in Russia rubble|author=|date=|work=bbc.co.uk}}</ref>
The explosion came two days after [[Vladimir Putin]] won [[Russian presidential election, 2004|reelection]] and several weeks after a [[suicide bombing]] killed 41 [[Moscow]] [[rapid transit|subway]] passengers.
In April 2004, authorities arrested and charged 26-year-old former employee of city gas services Sergey Alekseychik. On December 16, 2005 he was sentenced to 25 years in prison. According to the official version, Alekseychik was fired from his natural gas technician job several days prior to the explosion, and to get even with his former employers and the city he sabotaged the gas system thus causing the tragedy.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Мстиславская|first1=Мария|title=Заслуживает снисхождения : Обвиненного во взрыве дома в Архангельске приговорили к 25 годам колонии|url=https://lenta.ru/articles/2005/12/16/gas1/|accessdate=1 June 2017|publisher=Lenta.ru|date=15 December 2005}}</ref> == See also == *[[Arkhangelsk FSB office bombing]] ==References== {{reflist}}
