'''Oscar Rivas''' is a Paraguayan [[environmentalist]]. He was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 1992, jointly with [[Elias Diaz Peña]], for their efforts to protect the ecosystems of the [[Paraná River]] and the [[Paraguay River]], in particular consequences from the [[Yacyretá Dam]] project.<ref name=goldman>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/97 |title=South & Central America 2000. Elias Diaz Peña & Oscar Rivas. Paraguay. Rivers & Dams |publisher=Goldman Environmental Prize |accessdate=8 January 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110505060233/http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/97 |archivedate=5 May 2011 |df= }}</ref>

