The '''Panaviska Recreation Area''' is located on the bench of Panasivka mountain stream between villages of [[Korostiv (Skole Raion)|Korostiv]] and [[Kozyova]] in [[Skole Raion]]. This is on the 666-kilometer along the highway ('''{{Highway M (Ukraine)|06}}''')  Kyiv-Chop.

It is a favorite spot as residents of the area and the car tourists. Back in the 1880 there were building recreation centers for children. On the territory of rest has gazebos, tables with benches, parking.

Also, there had once been famous "Guta Korostivska",<ref>[http://carpathians.eu/?id=1860 Коростівська Гута] {{uk icon}}</ref> wherein worked 140 people. "Guta Korostivska" was once famous for its of glass products throughout Europe.

